notes:
# Power
- We need cash so  [Threads of Fate](item_cb61612b-9d83-49a9-989d-013bf084fbcb) is the absolute best power for farming money

# Weapon
- [Compensator](item_2a354f80-610c-4661-9bdd-8960ae1a60b0) and  [Weapon Grease](item_961ae72f-434f-406b-a89b-ab8efec806bf) are standard

# Ability
- Nothing here.

# Survival
- If they're running close range/speed with cass, jq, etc. then  [Armored Vest](item_358361e2-59be-4c81-b221-8a87f37809e6) is nice because your team is naturally gonna be playing close anyway.
- If they're running longer range, like with ashe and soldier, then  [First Aid Kit](item_0172eaaa-1902-44a3-b989-d12f0f7301da) is nice to survive poke dmg. 
- Also, if you have a more dps focused other support like lucio/moira,  [First Aid Kit](item_0172eaaa-1902-44a3-b989-d12f0f7301da) can help w/ you living without needing their peel.

# Weapon
- If you are rolling the enemy, the combo of  [Advanced Nanobiotics](item_26fcf7c9-b81a-4d8e-a459-b515519cb73e) and  [Talon Modification Module](item_c0ca1795-a3ea-4dc9-ae17-f34122574b3a) give the same WP as  [Amari's Antidote](item_67e0b1c5-3bcb-4ab5-b818-5082e5706124) but cost less so I usually go for that.

# Ability
- For Nepal and other more open maps,  [Angelic Acrobatics](item_baad85fc-3da5-43af-ad9d-f17885f59aa5) is nice but expensive. It makes it easier to stay away from non-hitscan enemy team.

# Survival
- Also after a round, get a feel for team tempo, if you feel like your team is playing fast or more split then  [Blessed Boosters](item_957fd380-b7b4-40d4-8333-bb8c535ca931) is super nice to get to everyone. This also helps if you specifically are being dove a lot, but also watch out for enemy hitscan! 
- If they have good hitscan, focus on WP because you're gonna play behind cover more anyway, so just buff your beam.

# Power
- If the team has good DPS and self-sustain pick  [Crepuscular Circle](item_c0b93ed2-b692-44d5-a38a-ce5a63e83cdb) the utility during ult also helps farm more money while letting you also DPS as mercy.
- If the team needs more support and heals then  [Triage Unit](item_fec0554c-2685-4b93-822d-bf0020e654b4) is really nice.

# Weapon
- The same combo of  [Advanced Nanobiotics](item_26fcf7c9-b81a-4d8e-a459-b515519cb73e) and  [Talon Modification Module](item_c0ca1795-a3ea-4dc9-ae17-f34122574b3a) is nice, or if you're really rich get  [Amari's Antidote](item_67e0b1c5-3bcb-4ab5-b818-5082e5706124) too.
- You can also go for either  [Caduceus Ex](item_9e7965ea-2abc-44a7-b042-950c6ad2fce7) if we have a more dive comp 

# Ability
- Nothing new here.

# Survival
- Besides that if its a more open map, like Collosseo, the armor from  [Vital-E-Tee](item_b92e6f1d-3aac-4eec-b027-00c8e1529016) is nice to survive poke because even if you move fast in GA there is less cover than Nepal.
- [Chain Evoker](item_812cc89e-feb0-47d0-9e03-9d8e33a80aca) only if you the DPS peel for you or if they get good picks

round_upgrades.notes: This makes mercy's ult way more useful. Also now you can battle mercy during it to get sneaky picks too!

notes:
# Weapon
- If tank and other teammates are getting too far away, then absolutely get  [Caduceus Ex](item_9e7965ea-2abc-44a7-b042-950c6ad2fce7) by now.

# Ability
- This depends a lot on the enemy team and basically vibe checking them.
- [Resurrection Rangefinder](item_99baffec-51b5-42e4-be61-e29f3de8219f) if you can get away with it, but if you are getting hard focused don't get it now and wait till next round.

# Survival
- If the enemy team is running a lot of WP, then combo  [Vital-E-Tee](item_b92e6f1d-3aac-4eec-b027-00c8e1529016) with  [Crusader Hydraulics](item_b64cee07-ca32-405d-987e-868b415bbc09) .  
- If they have a lot of AP, then  [Vishkar Condensor](item_086a91da-b65d-4047-8fc7-28a992078b1d) and  [Reinforced Titanium](item_8ebaa7db-aedf-48ed-adc1-318cb46a3214) is nice. 
- Finally, if you're super rich, then  [Martian Mender](item_0099632b-4e18-450e-844f-22c40e51bc98) is a super nice combo with the movement items.
- Also if you trust your DPS to get picks, once again  [Chain Evoker](item_812cc89e-feb0-47d0-9e03-9d8e33a80aca) helps you live by eliminating the other team.
- The goal here is to live, because at this point as long as you live you can keep at least one other teammate alive and turn a fight around.

round_upgrades.notes: This makes mercy's ult way more useful. Also now you can battle mercy during it to get sneaky picks too!

notes:
# Power
- This is where you can get really silly but once again it depends on your team and enemy team vibes.
- [Distortion](item_5557e2f2-02df-4eac-8128-0c23b71183b1) is the standard because not only does it help anyone you attach your beam to survive (they get the buff even when you are healing them!) but it also enables teammates to be a little more aggro and pull off nice picks, and it has constant uptime.
- For ultra survivability,  [First Responder](item_30a5c70f-e0b5-489a-96ae-900f34c3823d) is super nice, but you need to have  [Resurrection Rangefinder](item_99baffec-51b5-42e4-be61-e29f3de8219f) . It also helps you pull of a dangerous res and get the other person out so you don't both feed. 
- [Renaissance](item_a460f234-6434-4d47-99f9-d4a0b15cd591) right now is risky because it gives lots of ult uptime but often you don't have the survival items to go along with it. Also it confuses both your team and the enemy team a lot, which while useful to make the enemy team back off, your team might over extend to make use of that ult. (Basically like the Ana nano effect in normal ranked, where sometimes you nano someone just to help them live but they think they need to do something with that nano and get a kill and over-extend).

# Weapon
- At this point you might want to sell both  [Advanced Nanobiotics](item_26fcf7c9-b81a-4d8e-a459-b515519cb73e) and  [Talon Modification Module](item_c0ca1795-a3ea-4dc9-ae17-f34122574b3a) to get  [Amari's Antidote](item_67e0b1c5-3bcb-4ab5-b818-5082e5706124) if you need the space. 
- However, getting  [Booster Jets](item_a291de85-b6d9-43cf-b5da-f3184a156f48) is a nice buff to get instead if you don't need space.

# Ability
- Once again, only get  [Resurrection Rangefinder](item_99baffec-51b5-42e4-be61-e29f3de8219f) if you have enough survivability to pull it off and a Rez focused Power.
- Otherwise, mobility from  [Angelic Acrobatics](item_baad85fc-3da5-43af-ad9d-f17885f59aa5) is nice. Don't get both this and  [Blessed Boosters](item_957fd380-b7b4-40d4-8333-bb8c535ca931) though, since that's just wasted cash.

# Survival
- Check out the enemy team, keep either the  [Vital-E-Tee](item_b92e6f1d-3aac-4eec-b027-00c8e1529016) or  [Vishkar Condensor](item_086a91da-b65d-4047-8fc7-28a992078b1d) combo items based on whether they have a WP or AP focus and you can't live.
- If you can afford it  [Martian Mender](item_0099632b-4e18-450e-844f-22c40e51bc98) is better than the reduced DMG from AP or WP. 
- While if they don't have  [Codebreaker](item_caa96c7e-655f-4d03-9bd9-0f41937fec27)  [Ogundimu Reduction Field](item_b12daf48-069b-44c1-88fe-221cbcff664d) is amazing to top it off.
- Finally, if your other support is having a hard time peeling for you,  [Angeleisure Wear](item_00b53ed7-0768-442b-a2c3-8d19608c9391) is nice.

round_upgrades.notes: This makes mercy's ult way more useful. Also now you can battle mercy during it to get sneaky picks too!

notes:
# Weapon
- The core build should be done, now just add buffs to your buffs.  [Hardlight Accelerator](item_0390c8af-2a68-4da2-b876-93da32c3f448) is nice when you constantly have GA and build up stacks.
- If you need more space swap  [Talon Modification Module](item_c0ca1795-a3ea-4dc9-ae17-f34122574b3a) and [Hardlight Accelerator](item_0390c8af-2a68-4da2-b876-93da32c3f448) for  [Amari's Antidote](item_67e0b1c5-3bcb-4ab5-b818-5082e5706124) .

# Ability
- Here you can swap movement items and get  [Angelic Acrobatics](item_baad85fc-3da5-43af-ad9d-f17885f59aa5) for more movement with the cash. 

# Survival
- Check in with your team and enemy team.  
- [Martian Mender](item_0099632b-4e18-450e-844f-22c40e51bc98) is nice for more hitscan and poke dmg, plus the CD reduction lets you escape. 
- [Ogundimu Reduction Field](item_b12daf48-069b-44c1-88fe-221cbcff664d) is nice for pure tankiness and  [Angeleisure Wear](item_00b53ed7-0768-442b-a2c3-8d19608c9391) to help yourself when your other support can't reach you, especially if you're moving around a lot.

round_upgrades.notes: This makes mercy's ult way more useful. Also now you can battle mercy during it to get sneaky picks too!

notes:
# Power
- Pick whichever will suit teams needs more.
- [Renaissance](item_a460f234-6434-4d47-99f9-d4a0b15cd591) with CD reduction and  [Crepuscular Circle](item_c0b93ed2-b692-44d5-a38a-ce5a63e83cdb) is amazing for constant ult uptime
- [Distortion](item_5557e2f2-02df-4eac-8128-0c23b71183b1) if you didn't get it before for more aggressive teammates
- [First Responder](item_30a5c70f-e0b5-489a-96ae-900f34c3823d) just to help pull off with a sneaky rez.

# Weapon
- [Amari's Antidote](item_67e0b1c5-3bcb-4ab5-b818-5082e5706124) and  [Booster Jets](item_a291de85-b6d9-43cf-b5da-f3184a156f48) are a priority.
- [Hardlight Accelerator](item_0390c8af-2a68-4da2-b876-93da32c3f448) another great one with constant GAs
- [Caduceus Ex](item_9e7965ea-2abc-44a7-b042-950c6ad2fce7) is a staple here for the WP and range, because everyone wants to get really aggressive at this point.

# Ability
- [Angelic Acrobatics](item_baad85fc-3da5-43af-ad9d-f17885f59aa5) based on the enemy team. Selling this to change the speed in the final round can really throw off the enemy if they are used to your movements from before and cause them to over-flick.

# Survival
- [Chain Evoker](item_812cc89e-feb0-47d0-9e03-9d8e33a80aca) if you have good DPS
- [Resurrection Rangefinder](item_99baffec-51b5-42e4-be61-e29f3de8219f) if you have a rez Power
- [Martian Mender](item_0099632b-4e18-450e-844f-22c40e51bc98) and  [Angeleisure Wear](item_00b53ed7-0768-442b-a2c3-8d19608c9391) for self healing
- [Ogundimu Reduction Field](item_b12daf48-069b-44c1-88fe-221cbcff664d) for WP focus enemy/hitscan and if they don't have  [Codebreaker](item_caa96c7e-655f-4d03-9bd9-0f41937fec27) 
- [Divine Intervention](item_b5148b7f-8529-4b1b-a90c-5d7cf13f8f0c) for big bursts of dmg
